# Admin & Data

## Auth

- Use `src/lib/admin-auth.ts` (Edge-safe) and `src/lib/admin-session.ts` (cookies).
- Session cookie is an HMAC-signed token — never `admin_session=true`.
- Require `ADMIN_PASSWORD` plus `ADMIN_SESSION_SECRET` (legacy alias: `NEXTAUTH_SECRET`).
- All mutating API routes must call `isAdminAuthenticated()` before writes.
- Middleware protects `/admin` and `/admin/*` except `/admin/login`.

## Persistence

- Editable content lives in `src/data/*.json` (source of truth for admin).
- Static showcase content may stay in `src/data/*.ts` (timeline, CTF, labs, etc.).
- All JSON writes go through `src/lib/data-store.ts` — never raw `fs.writeFileSync` in routes.
- If `canPersistData()` is false (e.g. Vercel), return a clear error; do not silently no-op.

## Dual files

Admin-editable data is **JSON-canonical**. Matching `.ts` files only re-export JSON (types + `export const`). Do not maintain a second hand-edited object in `.ts`. Static-only content (timeline, CTF, labs) may stay TS-only.
